Van Gogh museum reopens in Amsterdam
2013-05-01 11:05:49 GMT
THE HAGUE, May 1 (Xinhua) -- After seven months of renovation, the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam reopened on Wednesday with an exhibition of Van Gogh at work.The Van Gogh at work anniversary exhibition is the result of extended research conducted by the museum into the artist's methods. The museum shows "how in 10 years' time the Dutch painter Vincent Van Gogh developed into a unique artist with an impressive oeuvre."Over 200 works of art provide insight into Van Gogh's way of working, including paintings, works on paper, letters and personal effects of the painter such as his original sketchbooks, paint tubes and only surviving palette, from the Musee d'Orsay in Paris.With the opening of the museum, all major tourist attractions at the Museum Square in Amsterdam, such as the recently opened museum of national art and history the Rijksmuseum, and the Dutch contemporary art museum the Stedelijk, are open for the first time in 10 years.
